                            <comment id="93726" author="guitarking117" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 00:06:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And, really, to be clear, after having spent over an hour now I&apos;m still not sure I got the &lt;tt&gt;AclPermissionEvaluator&lt;/tt&gt; configured correctly. I got that I needed to create the &lt;tt&gt;JdbcAclService&lt;/tt&gt;, but it needs a &lt;tt&gt;LookupStrategy&lt;/tt&gt;. Then &lt;tt&gt;BasicLookupStrategy&lt;/tt&gt; needs an &lt;tt&gt;AclCache&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;AclAuthorizationStrategy&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;PermissionGrantingStrategy&lt;/tt&gt;. &lt;tt&gt;AclAuthorizationStrategyImpl&lt;/tt&gt; is pretty easy. &lt;tt&gt;DefaultPermissionGrantingStrategy&lt;/tt&gt; needs an &lt;tt&gt;AuditLogger&lt;/tt&gt; ... not a lot of information about what this is for, but I figured it out eventually. &lt;tt&gt;AclCache&lt;/tt&gt; is a doozy. Looks like I have to figure up a fully-functional cache system. Really? Thankfully Spring offers the &lt;tt&gt;ConcurrentMapCache&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All told, the documentation is sorely lacking about how to get the ACL system configured. XML and Java config samples would be enormously helpful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="93737" author="rwinch" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 08:18:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=guitarking117&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;guitarking117&quot;&gt;Nick Williams&lt;/a&gt; Understood that the documentation (in general) needs updating. This is certainly something we have started to correct (i.e. you will notice we have started adding guides).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you search the samples for AclPermissionEvaluator you will find the contacts sample provides an XML based example of using ACLs. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
